      "id": "96a1465c394cb7b0",
      "item": {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "id": "96a1465c394cb7b0",
        "text": "My starting point is always: a deficit in the current intellectual landscape, which always leads to the fact that individual points of view are pulled up, and are then sold for the whole. People talk about the risk society or the information society, when they think they can better understand everything via the computer, or the distributional injustice of economic prosperity as the central problem of modern society. But how does this judgment come about? The question is: How does someone know that this is what matters and nothing else? And I think that this is simply insufficient compared to the possible intellectual approaches, and one could do better. That also means that a lot of, a lot of zeal, a lot of indignation discourages, doesn't it? And says, well, all right. It doesn't mean that you cover up or don't discover grievances. When you see how people live in favelas, there is already reason to think. And a social theory that is not able to understand the relationship between globalization on the level of functional large-scale systems on the one hand and the grievances of a regional nature on the other hand... If this cannot occur as a topic, something is wrong."
      },
